Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure size limits in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Override Kestrel's default 30MB limit to 10MB
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
{
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
});

// Also configure form options (multipart body length limit)
builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
{
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

**Add the endpoint (after `app.UseAntiforgery()`):**

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    // Validate content type
    string[] allowed = ["image/jpeg", "image/png"];
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    // Validate size (defense-in-depth; Kestrel limit also enforces this)
    const long maxSize = 10L * 1024 * 1024;
    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File must be 10 MB or smaller.");

    // Build a safe file name to prevent path traversal
    var uploadsDir = Path.Combine(Directory.GetCurrentDirectory(), "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsDir);

    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (ext is not ".jpg" and not ".jpeg" and not ".png")
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid file extension.");

    var savedName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var filePath = Path.Combine(uploadsDir, savedName);

    await using var stream = new FileStream(filePath, FileMode.Create);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName = savedName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // see note below
```

**Why `.DisableAntiforgery()`?** — Since your pipeline calls `UseAntiforgery()`, every `IFormFile`-binding endpoint requires a valid antiforgery token by default. API clients (mobile apps, SPAs, Postman) typically don't send one. `.DisableAntiforgery()` opts this single endpoint out; protect it with JWT/API-key auth instead. If your callers *do* send the token (e.g., a Razor form), remove that call.

**Key defenses:**

| Layer | What it stops |
|---|---|
| Kestrel `MaxRequestBodySize` | Oversized requests killed before buffering |
| `MultipartBodyLengthLimit` | Same limit at the form-parsing layer |
| Content-type + extension check | Blocks non-image uploads |
| `Guid` file name | Prevents path traversal & name collisions |
